Lab Scinario:
The /etc/passwd file contains information about user accounts. It is world-readable, but usually only writable by the root user.
ls -l /etc/passwd

Steps:
I.Generate a new password hash with a password of your choice:
openssl passwd ur101g

II.Edit the /etc/passwd file and place the generated password hash between the first and second colon (:) of the root
user's row (replacing the "x").

III. su root


